1. Power Failure
Issue: The computer does not turn on when the power button is pressed.
Causes
Loose power cable
Faulty power supply (SMPS)
Dead battery (laptops)
Faulty power button
✅ Solutions
[ ] Check the power cable
[ ] Ensure the power supply is working
[ ] Charge or replace the laptop battery
[ ] Test the power button
2. No Display
Issue: The PC powers on, but the monitor shows a blank screen.
Causes
Loose monitor cable
Faulty RAM
Graphics card issue
✅ Solutions
[ ] Check monitor connection
[ ] Reseat the RAM
[ ] Check the graphics card
[ ] Test with another monitor
3. Operating System Not Found
Issue: BIOS/UEFI cannot locate a bootable operating system.
Causes
Incorrect boot priority
Missing operating system
Damaged hard drive
✅ Solutions
[ ] Set the correct boot device in BIOS
[ ] Repair Windows using installation media
[ ] Replace the hard disk if damaged
4. Blue Screen Error (BSOD)
Issue: Windows crashes with a blue screen during boot.
Causes
Driver problems
Hardware failure
Corrupted system files
✅ Solutions
[ ] Update device drivers
[ ] Run Startup Repair
[ ] Scan for corrupted system files
[ ] Replace faulty hardware if required
5. Continuous Restart Loop
Issue: The PC keeps restarting without loading Windows.
Causes
Corrupted Windows files
Faulty RAM
Hardware failure
✅ Solutions
[ ] Boot into Safe Mode
[ ] Repair Windows
[ ] Test RAM
[ ] Reinstall Windows if necessary
6. BIOS/UEFI Not Detecting Hard Disk
Issue: Hard drive is not detected during boot.
Causes
Loose SATA cable
Damaged hard disk
BIOS settings problem
✅ Solutions
[ ] Reconnect SATA and power cables
[ ] Enable the drive in BIOS
[ ] Replace the hard drive if faulty
7. Boot Device Not Found
Issue: The computer cannot find a bootable device.
Causes
Incorrect boot priority
Missing operating system
Damaged hard drive
✅ Solutions
[ ] Set the correct boot priority order
[ ] Repair or reinstall the operating system
[ ] Replace the damaged storage device
